                <h6><a name="ecologycal">ECOLOGICAL GAP ANALYSIS OF PROTECTED AREAS</a></h6>
              <p>Through their national ecological gap analyses, countries have identified high priority sites (HiPs) to expand or improve their protected area systems and networks. In many cases, the assessment yields spatial data identifying ‘gaps’ in the current protected area system, i.e. areas of importance for biodiversity conservation that are not yet officially recognised as protected areas, or where management can be improved. The Carbon Calculator includes spatial data from ecological gap analyses in Brazil, Ecuador Mexico, and Peru.</p>
              <a  class="butt" href="/data#ecologycal"><span>VIEW DATA SOURCES</span></a>
